# 🚀 ML Model Detection

A collection of machine learning projects focused on real-world detection tasks using computer vision and deep learning.

---

## 📌 Overview

This repository contains multiple ML-based detection models developed using Python and Google Colab. These projects demonstrate practical applications like:

- 🚗 Number Plate Detection  
- 🚘 Seatbelt Detection  
- 📊 Experimental ML models  

---

## 🧠 Projects Included

### 🔢 Number Plate Detection
- Detects vehicle number plates from images/videos  
- Uses object detection techniques  
- Can be extended for OCR-based recognition  

### 🪑 Seatbelt Detection
- Classifies whether a person is wearing a seatbelt or not  
- Built using deep learning models (YOLO / CNN-based)  
- Useful for traffic safety monitoring systems  

### 📁 Other Notebooks
- `Untitled2.ipynb` – Experimental / testing notebook  

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- Python 🐍  
- Google Colab ☁️  
- OpenCV  
- TensorFlow / PyTorch  
- YOLO (Object Detection)  

---

## 📂 Repository Structure

```
ML-MODEL-DETECTION/
│── Number_Plate.ipynb
│── Seatbelts_training.ipynb
│── Untitled2.ipynb
│── README.md
```

---

## ▶️ How to Run

1. Clone the repository  
```
git clone https://github.com/Praneetha-as29/ML-MODEL-DETECTION.git
```

2. Open notebooks in Google Colab or Jupyter Notebook  

3. Install dependencies (if required)  
```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

4. Run all cells step-by-step  

